    "comment_id" : 88402480,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "@OlivierGr&#233;goire the array doesn’t need to be <code>String[]</code>. If it is <code>Object[]</code> and you do <code>array[expression] += &quot;foo&quot;;</code>, it’s the same. But yes, it doesn’t apply to primitive arrays, as it must be able to hold references of type <code>String</code> (<code>Object[]</code>, <code>CharSequence[]</code>, <code>Comparable[]</code>, …), to store the result of string concatenation."
